<div id="review_2409022543" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2409022543" />
    <a title="Celia" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/30261451-celia"><img alt="Celia" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1637173851p2/30261451.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2409022543?book_show_action=true">Sep 08, 2021</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Celia" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Celia" href="/user/show/30261451-celia">Celia</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Kindle Edition " href="/book/show/16135533-the-intuitionist">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/30261451-celia?shelf=ten-year-challenge">ten-year-challenge</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/30261451-celia?shelf=kindle-library">kindle-library</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/30261451-celia?shelf=great-american-reads">great-american-reads</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/30261451-celia?shelf=2021-kindle-counted">2021-kindle-counted</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/30261451-celia?shelf=2021-read">2021-read</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/30261451-celia?shelf=2021-su-rcc">2021-su-rcc</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2409022543" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer17840502667758941641">I have read two books by Colson Whitehead, both Pulitzer Prize winners: <a href='https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/30555488.The_Underground_Railroad' title='The Underground Railroad by Colson Whitehead' rel='nofollow noopener'>The Underground Railroad</a> and <a href='https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/42270835.The_Nickel_Boys' title='The Nickel Boys by Colson Whitehead' rel='nofollow noopener'>The Nickel Boys</a><br/><br/>Nothing in either of those two books prepared me for the premise or prose of <a href='https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/16271.The_Intuitionist' title='The Intuitionist by Colson Whitehead' rel='nofollow noopener'>The Intuitionist</a>.<br/><br/>The Premise: Elevator Inspectors who belong to two schools of thought: Intuitionists and Empiricists. The Intuitionists practice an inspecting method by which they ride in an elevator and intuit the state of the elevator and its related systems. The competing school, the &quot;Empiricists&quot;, ins</span>
  <span id="freeText17840502667758941641" style="display:none">I have read two books by Colson Whitehead, both Pulitzer Prize winners: <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/30555488.The_Underground_Railroad" title="The Underground Railroad by Colson Whitehead" rel="nofollow noopener">The Underground Railroad</a> and <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/42270835.The_Nickel_Boys" title="The Nickel Boys by Colson Whitehead" rel="nofollow noopener">The Nickel Boys</a><br /><br />Nothing in either of those two books prepared me for the premise or prose of <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/16271.The_Intuitionist" title="The Intuitionist by Colson Whitehead" rel="nofollow noopener">The Intuitionist</a>.<br /><br />The Premise: Elevator Inspectors who belong to two schools of thought: Intuitionists and Empiricists. The Intuitionists practice an inspecting method by which they ride in an elevator and intuit the state of the elevator and its related systems. The competing school, the "Empiricists", insists upon traditional instrument-based verification of the condition of the elevator. Lila Mae Watson, our heroine, is the second black inspector and the first black female inspector in the city.<br /><br />Watson is an Intuitionist. She has recently inspected an elevator which has experienced a catastrophic failure. Watson has probably been set up by the current President of the Elevator Guild, Frank Chancre (Empiricist)<br /><br />This is the 100th book I have finished this year and it is MORE THAN worthy of such a distinction.<br /><br />5 stars</span>
  <a data-text-id="17840502667758941641" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


